<div class="flex flex-col gap-5">
	<p>
		Taking place at Higher Ground, an industrial complex on the outskirts of Lisbon that has become a cornerstone of the city’s underground scene. Thirteen artists—active participants in the global electronic music community as digital creators, producers, and musicians—presented works spanning digital art, photography, music production, and video. Their pieces explored both the raw energy of electronic music and the broader cultural movement of collective expression.
    </p>

    <p>With rave culture rooted in personal and identity expression, the works addressed themes such as fluid bodies, queerness and the celebration of the strange and disorienting. These themes reflect what rave communities seek in these spaces—often distant from their everyday social realities—where they can explore, express, and feel through a communal experience.</p>
</div>
